<!-- Adding Markers
=========================================== -->
<h3 id="AddingMarkers" class="ui header">Adding markers</h3>
<p>
  Every marker must be assigned an id when it is added to the map.
  If an id is not specified, gmaps will autogenerate one for you.
  All default <a href="#Settings">settings</a> can be overwritten by passing in an object.
</p>
<%= code_segment "myMap.<bl>add</bl>(<s>marker</s>, {\n" +
  "  id: <s>myMarker</s>,\n" +
  "  position: {\n" + 
  "    lat: <o>51.178835</o>,\n" + 
  "    lng: <o>-1.826240</o>\n" + 
  "  }\n" +
  "})"
%>

<p>To add multiple markers at once, you can pass in an array of options as the second parameter.</p>
<%= code_segment "myMap.<bl>add</bl>(<s>markers</s>, [\n" +
  "  {\n" +
  "    id: <s>myMarker</s>,\n" +
  "    center: {\n" + 
  "      lat: <o>51.178835</o>,\n" + 
  "      lng: <o>-1.826240</o>\n" + 
  "    }\n" +
  "  },\n" +
  "  ...\n" +
  "])"
%>


<!-- Setting Options
=========================================== -->
<h3 id="SettingOptions" class="ui header">Setting options</h3>
<p>
  To set options after initialization, specify the option and value.
  You can set multiple options at once by passing in an object as the only parameter.
</p>
<%= code_segment "<c>set single option</c>\n" +
  "myMap.<bl>markers</bl>().<bl>setOptions</bl>(<s>draggable</s>, <o>true</o>)\n\n" +
  "<c>set multiple options</c>\n" +
  "myMap.<bl>markers</bl>().<bl>setOptions</bl>({\n" +
  "  draggable: <o>true</o>,\n" +
  "  opacity: <o>1</o>\n" +
  "})"
%>


<!-- Getting Options
=========================================== -->
<h3 id="GettingOptions" class="ui header">Getting options</h3>
<p>
  To get the value of a specifc option, pass in the option name.
  If you do not supply an option name, all the options will be returned in an object.
</p>
<%= code_segment "<c>get single option</c>\n" +
  "myMap.<bl>markers</bl>().<bl>getOptions</bl>(<s>opacity</s>)\n\n" +
  "<c>get all options</c>\n" +
  "myMap.<bl>markers</bl>().<bl>getOptions</bl>()"
%>


